Since $BE = 10\sqrt{7}$, triangle $BOE$ is equilateral. Therefore, $\angle BOE = 60^\circ$, and $\angle COE = 120^\circ$.

Since $CO = 10\sqrt{21}$, triangle $COE$ is a 30-60-90 triangle. Thus, $CE = 2\cdot CO = 20\sqrt{21}$ and $OE = \frac{CO}{\sqrt{3}} = \frac{10\sqrt{21}}{\sqrt{3}} = 10\sqrt{7}$.

Finally, since $\angle CFO = 90^\circ$, we have  \[EF = CE - CF = CE - OE = 20\sqrt{21} - 10\sqrt{7} = 10\sqrt{7}(2\sqrt{3} - 1).\]

